{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_6","type":"agent_message","text":"Yes. Free-text alone is weak here.\n\nThis app already has the right pattern on the sessions screen: it loads known folders server-side and exposes them as a `<select>` plus a `datalist`-backed text input in [src/routes/app/sessions/+page.server.ts:17](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/routes/app/sessions/+page.server.ts#L17) and [src/routes/app/sessions/+page.svelte:217](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/routes/app/sessions/+page.svelte#L217). The clean fix is to reuse that for the project form in [src/routes/app/projects/+page.server.ts:11](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/routes/app/projects/+page.server.ts#L11) and [src/routes/app/projects/+page.svelte:83](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/routes/app/projects/+page.svelte#L83).\n\nThe implementation I’d make is:\n- Move the folder discovery logic out of the sessions route into a shared server helper.\n- Return `folderOptions` from the projects page load.\n- For each directory field, add:\n  - a “Pick a known folder” select\n  - the existing text input with `list=...` so users can still paste/type\n  - selection wiring so picking an option fills the input\n- Keep repo URL as plain text, but give `defaultRepoPath` the same picker treatment.\n\nI would not use a browser-native `<input type=\"file\" webkitdirectory\">` here. In a web app it does not cleanly give you stable absolute server paths, which is what this form is storing. A server-backed directory picker/select is the correct model for this app.\n\nI can implement it, but the workspace is currently read-only, so I can’t patch the files in this turn."}}
